1
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:16,000
I wanted to deal
with her myself.

2
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:18,500
But I don't want to fail
and end up in jail again.

3
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:20,600
I don't want him to know
that we're doing something

4
00:00:20,667 --> 00:00:22,033
against that woman.

5
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:23,433
When you make it out alive,

6
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:26,900
please tell my parents
I love them.

7
00:00:26,967 --> 00:00:28,767
You will tell them yourself.

8
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:30,100
You will make it home, Red.

9
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:32,667
I suffered for so many years
because of what they did to me.

10
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:34,800
I couldn't fight at that time
because I was in jail.

11
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:36,033
But the situation
is different now.

12
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:39,033
I won't let them
mistreat me again!

13
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:40,600
I'm just going to get something.

14
00:00:40,667 --> 00:00:41,633
- I'll be right back.
- Don't leave me.

15
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,100
I'll be right back.

16
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:44,667
Please...

17
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:45,533
Yen.

18
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:48,067
Someone's waiting
for you, Yen.

19
00:00:48,133 --> 00:00:49,867
You need to get through this.

20
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:53,000
You can do this, Eden!

21
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:54,367
Never give up!

22
00:01:03,900 --> 00:01:04,700
Yes!

23
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:14,767
Red!

24
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:16,400
Sorry I didn't
know it was you.

25
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:18,533
Are you feeling
better now?

26
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:19,833
You almost hit me.

27
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:21,633
You're all better now!

28
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:22,633
Red, you're better now!

29
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:24,100
You're better now!

30
00:01:27,233 --> 00:01:28,900
Thank you, Lord!

31
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:37,167
We're still lucky...

32
00:01:37,233 --> 00:01:41,900
to find a new house to rent.

33
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,333
I feel shy toward
Lulu and her family.

34
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:48,400
We stayed with them
for almost three days.

35
00:01:51,867 --> 00:01:53,200
Are you okay, Amanda?

36
00:01:58,267 --> 00:02:00,767
You've been quiet.

37
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:04,967
I feel ashamed.

38
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:08,367
I know you're not
used to trouble.

39
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:11,600
You've hated fights ever
since we were young.

40
00:02:11,667 --> 00:02:14,600
But now that we're together,

41
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:17,467
I'm dragging you into my mess.

42
00:02:17,533 --> 00:02:18,733
I'm sorry.

43
00:02:19,467 --> 00:02:22,100
Come on, I never think of that.

44
00:02:25,733 --> 00:02:28,800
And you know, I understand.

45
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:30,933
I know what you're
going through.

46
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,167
So don't worry about it.

47
00:02:33,133 --> 00:02:36,067
I can't help it.

48
00:02:36,133 --> 00:02:40,167
And it's really embarrassing.

49
00:02:40,233 --> 00:02:44,667
You have an ex-convict sister.

50
00:02:44,733 --> 00:02:46,233
Convicted.

51
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:47,200
A criminal.

52
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:49,133
But we both know
that you're innocent.

53
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,333
You didn't do
anything wrong.

54
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,600
Period.

55
00:02:51,667 --> 00:02:52,733
It's just the two of us.

56
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,233
No one else knows that.

57
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:56,533
People around us
don't know that.

58
00:02:57,933 --> 00:03:00,967
They see me the same
way Rina sees me.

59
00:03:01,033 --> 00:03:04,867
She still treats
me as a criminal.

60
00:03:04,933 --> 00:03:06,533
That's why she doesn't
want to leave us alone.

61
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:13,067
Stop thinking about the
negative things, please.

62
00:03:13,133 --> 00:03:16,367
Forget about Rina.

63
00:03:16,433 --> 00:03:17,833
She'll get tired eventually.

64
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:23,133
Do you think she'll deal with us
first over her missing child?

65
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:30,333
I know that you, me, and Yenyen
we'll reunite someday.

66
00:03:32,033 --> 00:03:33,967
We will be complete again.

67
00:03:34,033 --> 00:03:35,600
And we will be happier.

68
00:03:35,667 --> 00:03:36,367
I promise.

69
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:40,100
So don't be sad.

70
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,233
It will happen.

71
00:03:51,533 --> 00:03:52,567
Red...

72
00:03:55,067 --> 00:04:03,900
Wherever you are, may you always
be protected from any harm.

73
00:04:06,567 --> 00:04:14,733
I pray that you will
come back to us alive.

74
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,233
I miss you so much.

75
00:04:37,267 --> 00:04:38,400
Yes, Zandro?

76
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:45,767
I'm not done with Amanda yet.

77
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:51,367
You still have a lot
of things to do.

78
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,367
Red!

79
00:05:19,767 --> 00:05:20,500
You might get sick again.

80
00:05:20,567 --> 00:05:21,967
Go and get some rest.

81
00:05:22,033 --> 00:05:23,500
No, I'm okay.

82
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:27,600
We've been wanting to
have a fire, right?

83
00:05:27,667 --> 00:05:28,967
We might make
a fire today.

84
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,967
Okay, go take your
medicines first.

85
00:05:39,733 --> 00:05:40,800
Here.

86
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:43,267
So you'll recover fully.

87
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:45,500
Here's the water.

88
00:05:52,433 --> 00:05:53,800
Yen,

89
00:05:53,867 --> 00:05:54,633
thank you.

90
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,467
If not for you, I
won't get better.

91
00:05:59,133 --> 00:06:00,833
Where did you get
that medicine?

92
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:02,267
It's better not to know.

93
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:03,600
You might get a fever
again if you do.

94
00:06:04,567 --> 00:06:05,300
You know what?

95
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,633
I'll just help you with that.

96
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:09,533
Okay.

97
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:19,300
Hurry up!

98
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:20,933
We're close to making it.

99
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,700
There it is!

100
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:23,400
I can already
see the smoke.

101
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:26,233
Hurry up.

102
00:06:35,967 --> 00:06:38,667
There it is. I can see an ember!

103
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:42,900
Just a bit more.

104
00:06:42,967 --> 00:06:52,933
There's the smoke!

105
00:07:29,567 --> 00:07:31,233
I'm going to find
something to eat.

106
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:35,433
I'll go get a rock we
can use for cooking.

107
00:08:26,367 --> 00:08:27,700
Is there any news about Red?

108
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:31,233
That's also what
they said yesterday.

109
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:34,267
They're doing everything,
but nothing good is happening.

110
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:36,900
My God, they're
all useless!

111
00:08:36,967 --> 00:08:39,367
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

112
00:08:39,433 --> 00:08:41,733
Victor, I'm sorry.

113
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:43,533
I didn't mean to
take it out on you.

114
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,333
I'm sorry, Victor.

115
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:47,867
I will see you later, okay?

116
00:08:47,933 --> 00:08:51,267
Yes, I just have to
finish something.

117
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:52,433
All right.

118
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:53,433
Bye.

119
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:09,133
Is there still no
news about Red?

120
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,767
Nothing.

121
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:11,733
They say the same thing.

122
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,500
They're doing everything.

123
00:09:13,567 --> 00:09:17,300
I want to curse at that search
and rescue operation team!

124
00:09:17,367 --> 00:09:18,267
Useless!

125
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:20,633
Rina, don't do that.

126
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:22,500
It won't help.

127
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:25,133
Just take it all
out on Amanda.

128
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:28,867
The thing that we
talked about...

129
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:31,633
I want you to do that...

130
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:34,333
as soon as possible.

131
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:41,733
I won't let them
have a peaceful life.

132
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,967
I know what to do, Rina.

133
00:09:44,033 --> 00:09:45,267
I'll handle it.

134
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:01,167
We've been here for
quite a while now.

135
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:03,400
And we haven't
caught any fish.

136
00:10:03,467 --> 00:10:05,533
Chill. We will catch fish.

137
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,433
Okay?

138
00:10:07,967 --> 00:10:09,500
You shouldn't fish
near the beach.

139
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:11,167
You should fish out there.

140
00:10:11,233 --> 00:10:12,233
You won't find
any fish here.

141
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:15,133
There are corals near here.

142
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,300
If you see corals,
definitely there's fish.

143
00:10:17,367 --> 00:10:19,100
So, there are fishes here.

144
00:10:19,167 --> 00:10:21,533
Go on. Show me that fish.

145
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:22,700
Okay.

146
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:24,833
You'll see a fish. Watch me.

147
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:34,767
Let's see what you've got.

148
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:49,700
Yen, something's moving.

149
00:10:53,367 --> 00:10:56,500
I can see something.

150
00:10:58,933 --> 00:10:59,800
Go, Red!

151
00:11:03,933 --> 00:11:06,133
Red, you found a big one.

152
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,800
Looks like it's branded!

153
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:12,667
This is really it. Wait for it.

154
00:11:12,733 --> 00:11:13,667
Relax, okay?
Here it is.

155
00:11:24,967 --> 00:11:26,800
Gross! What's that?

156
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:32,100
Oh, you find it funny?

157
00:11:32,167 --> 00:11:35,167
Let's see if you can
still laugh at this.

158
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:36,133
What's that?

159
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,633
Come on, let's go back.

160
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:38,600
What is it?

161
00:11:39,300 --> 00:11:39,833
This!

162
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:40,900
Red!

163
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:42,967
Red!

164
00:11:43,867 --> 00:11:45,633
Let's go!

165
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:47,167
You haven't caught
anything anyway.

166
00:11:47,233 --> 00:11:48,000
Come on!

167
00:11:48,067 --> 00:11:50,400
Yen, I feel that
I will catch one.

168
00:11:50,467 --> 00:11:51,633
I saw a big fish earlier.

169
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,067
Go, Red!

170
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:58,467
Get it!

171
00:11:58,533 --> 00:12:00,100
Red, it's fish!

172
00:12:00,167 --> 00:12:01,233
It's so big!

173
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:02,533
You're so great!

174
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,733
You're great, Red!

175
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:04,833
Yes!

176
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,233
We got one!

177
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,833
Ma'am Josie,
I'll go ahead.

178
00:12:20,900 --> 00:12:21,967
Okay.

179
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:24,533
I still have to
wait for my husband.

180
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,933
Dindi, come to work
early tomorrow, okay?

181
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,933
- It's your contract renewal.
- Of course.

182
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,333
It's the end of your
contract today.

183
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,600
I'll be here first
thing in the morning.

184
00:12:33,667 --> 00:12:35,067
Okay, be safe.

185
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:35,967
- You, too.
- Okay.
Thank you.

186
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,500
Is Dindi working for you?

187
00:12:58,967 --> 00:13:00,567
Why?

188
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,067
Fire her.

189
00:13:04,133 --> 00:13:05,333
Do you understand?

190
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,267
Why would I do that?

191
00:13:09,167 --> 00:13:11,567
Do as I say,

192
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:16,600
or you and your family will get
involved.

193
00:13:17,567 --> 00:13:18,933
Do you understand?

194
00:14:16,967 --> 00:14:18,533
Surprise!

195
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,833
Buffet!

196
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:22,467
So that's why I couldn't
find you earlier.

197
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:24,733
You were busy doing this.

198
00:14:25,667 --> 00:14:26,800
It looks delicious.

199
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:27,967
Thank you.

200
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:32,667
I'm just making it up to you
for taking care of me.

201
00:14:35,633 --> 00:14:36,467
You should start eating.

202
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:39,100
I cooked it myself.

203
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:41,533
Here.

204
00:14:48,767 --> 00:14:49,600
Wait.
I'll do it.

205
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:53,333
There you go.

206
00:14:57,367 --> 00:14:58,467
It's good.

207
00:15:07,467 --> 00:15:08,500
Yen, go on and eat.

208
00:15:08,567 --> 00:15:09,900
I removed the bones already.

209
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:13,967
I'm so spoiled.

210
00:15:14,033 --> 00:15:15,033
You still remove the fish
bones for me

211
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:17,067
even though I'm already
a grownup.

212
00:15:17,133 --> 00:15:19,400
Of course. I'm an expert
on this.

213
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:21,200
Here, eat.

214
00:15:21,267 --> 00:15:22,667
Take a bite.

215
00:15:23,533 --> 00:15:24,300
Here.

216
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:34,233
Let me do it.

217
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:36,533
I brought that for you.

218
00:15:38,367 --> 00:15:39,433
You should eat too.

219
00:15:42,167 --> 00:15:42,933
Here, Mom.

220
00:15:47,033 --> 00:15:48,267
There are no bones.

221
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:54,133
Why?

222
00:15:55,900 --> 00:15:57,867
I just remembered my mom.

223
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:02,800
She removes the fish bones
for me all the time.

224
00:16:04,867 --> 00:16:08,733
Yenyen, my dear,
have some of this fish.

225
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:10,033
Is she like that?

226
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:14,333
But seriously,

227
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:16,200
I miss my mom.

228
00:16:17,867 --> 00:16:19,367
I know how you feel.

229
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:24,333
Don't worry.

230
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,733
We'll get the raft
done tomorrow.

231
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:28,300
So...

232
00:16:28,367 --> 00:16:29,933
we can leave this place.

233
00:16:31,933 --> 00:16:34,133
Thank you...

234
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,133
for being here, Red.

235
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:40,300
Thank you...

236
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:42,833
for being with me
on this island.

237
00:16:56,733 --> 00:16:58,733
Yes! I will get that bag.

238
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:01,333
I will transfer the money,
and then tomorrow,

239
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:03,067
I will tell my driver
to pick it up.

240
00:17:03,133 --> 00:17:03,900
Okay.

241
00:17:03,967 --> 00:17:05,167
Thank you.

242
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:10,200
What are you doing here?

243
00:17:10,267 --> 00:17:11,967
You could have just called.

244
00:17:12,033 --> 00:17:13,833
You're so stubborn.

245
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:15,000
Did you do it?

246
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:16,800
Yes, Rina.

247
00:17:16,867 --> 00:17:19,133
Amanda's sister is now jobless.

248
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,500
Keep it down.

249
00:17:20,567 --> 00:17:22,067
Victor might hear us.

250
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:26,133
But make sure you did it.

251
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,800
I'm very sure of it.

252
00:17:27,867 --> 00:17:30,933
So don't forget the extra
that I asked you for.

253
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,833
Have you collected the money
from Mr. Romero?

254
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:35,800
Yes, Rina.

255
00:17:35,867 --> 00:17:36,933
Collected with interest.

256
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,300
Deposited in your account.

257
00:17:39,367 --> 00:17:40,867
Don't you check your account?

258
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,400
I will transfer the money
into your account.

259
00:17:43,467 --> 00:17:44,833
But you should go.

260
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:45,933
Victor might see us.

261
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:46,833
I don't want him to catch us.

262
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:49,000
Go, go, go. Okay.

263
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:50,933
Okay. Bye, Rina.

264
00:17:57,600 --> 00:18:01,167
Are you sure you want to work?

265
00:18:01,233 --> 00:18:02,300
Yes.

266
00:18:02,367 --> 00:18:07,133
I met a supplier of rice cakes
on the street.

267
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:09,400
I told her...

268
00:18:09,467 --> 00:18:10,733
I would sell it.

269
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:14,833
I haven't seen anyone selling
rice cakes in our neighborhood.

270
00:18:15,967 --> 00:18:19,467
But I'm not asking you to work.

271
00:18:19,533 --> 00:18:20,500
I know.

272
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:23,600
But I need to do something.

273
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:28,500
Instead of just sitting here
while waiting for Yenyen,

274
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:29,967
I should prepare for her return.

275
00:18:30,033 --> 00:18:30,767
Right?

276
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:35,033
I want to support my child
this time.

277
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:39,133
I want to provide for her needs.

278
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:44,367
I know there's no guarantee
that she'll come back.

279
00:18:46,067 --> 00:18:52,400
But I can feel in my heart
that my daughter is alive.

280
00:18:52,467 --> 00:18:55,800
Several days might have passed,

281
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:58,967
but I feel she'll come back
to us.

282
00:19:00,633 --> 00:19:02,400
God is generous.

283
00:19:02,467 --> 00:19:06,800
I know he will let me
see my daughter again.

284
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:30,600
The sky is full of stars,
isn't it?

285
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:34,567
It's only now
that I appreciate its beauty.

286
00:19:38,133 --> 00:19:42,433
We were so busy when
we were in Manila.

287
00:19:44,733 --> 00:19:46,633
There are a lot of distractions.

288
00:19:47,867 --> 00:19:50,500
We don't have time spare time...

289
00:19:51,667 --> 00:19:52,967
To think...

290
00:19:54,667 --> 00:19:55,967
To rest...

291
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:59,000
To chill...

292
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:04,767
And appreciate
the simple things.

293
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,300
But do you know what
I appreciate most,

294
00:20:11,367 --> 00:20:12,533
on this island?

295
00:20:15,167 --> 00:20:16,800
It's having you here...

296
00:20:18,033 --> 00:20:19,067
right now.

297
00:20:21,833 --> 00:20:25,100
If there's anything good
that happened on this island,

298
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:28,500
that would be you.

299
00:20:31,033 --> 00:20:32,833
Having found you...

300
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:35,367
Knowing you...

301
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:42,033
Your boyfriend must be lucky.

302
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:45,533
What boyfriend?

303
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,167
I don't have one.

304
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:51,533
Really?

305
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:52,600
Yes.

306
00:20:54,267 --> 00:20:55,167
What happened?

307
00:20:55,233 --> 00:20:56,833
Did you break up?

308
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,600
How is that even possible?

309
00:20:58,667 --> 00:21:00,467
I haven't had a boyfriend.

310
00:21:02,667 --> 00:21:03,667
As in never?

311
00:21:04,633 --> 00:21:06,200
Since birth.

312
00:21:11,933 --> 00:21:15,933
That's why we have to get out
of this island.

313
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:20,433
I don't want to die without
having a boyfriend.

314
00:21:21,933 --> 00:21:23,600
Then...

315
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:25,267
get a boyfriend here.

316
00:21:26,300 --> 00:21:27,300
How can I do that?

317
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:29,133
You're the only man here.

318
00:21:30,233 --> 00:21:31,233
You're lucky.

319
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,767
Crazy.

320
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:40,900
Who wouldn't get crazy over you?

321
00:21:45,033 --> 00:21:46,833
Is that a pickup line?

322
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:49,400
Tell me. I'm ready to laugh.

323
00:21:53,433 --> 00:21:54,333
Thank you.

324
00:21:56,300 --> 00:21:58,400
Thank you for taking care of me.

325
00:22:00,133 --> 00:22:02,367
Thank you that I have met you.

326
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,567
Thank you for everything.

327
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:52,600
Sorry, I just got carried away.

328
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:57,800
I'm not used to it.

329
00:22:57,867 --> 00:23:00,267
I haven't had a boyfriend,
remember?

330
00:23:02,067 --> 00:23:05,333
I haven't yet experienced going
to a party with a date.

331
00:23:07,500 --> 00:23:08,800
Are you kidding?

332
00:23:10,833 --> 00:23:12,167
Of course not.

333
00:23:12,233 --> 00:23:13,467
We're not well-off.

334
00:23:14,867 --> 00:23:19,633
Instead of wasting my time
partying, I was working.

335
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:25,333
I didn't even experience
going to the JS Prom.

336
00:23:28,067 --> 00:23:29,433
Poor you.

337
00:23:40,267 --> 00:23:41,167
What's that?

338
00:23:42,533 --> 00:23:45,533
You didn't experience going
to the JS Prom, right?

339
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:50,467
Maybe this is the perfect moment
to experience it.

340
00:23:52,533 --> 00:23:54,400
Yen,

341
00:23:54,467 --> 00:23:56,000
can I have this dance?

342
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:17,733
It's not easy to dance
without music.

343
00:24:19,967 --> 00:24:23,100
Concentrate, and you'll hear it.

344
00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:28,000
Close your eyes.

345
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:32,200
Do you hear it?

346
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:35,700
Yes.

347
00:24:36,900 --> 00:24:38,167
It's nice.

348
00:25:12,533 --> 00:25:14,100
Do you hear it?

349
00:25:14,167 --> 00:25:16,800
The music seems to get faster.

350
00:25:16,867 --> 00:25:17,533
What?

351
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:18,600
The music is getting faster.

352
00:25:18,667 --> 00:25:19,333
Really?

353
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:20,800
Yes, the beat is faster now.

354
00:25:20,867 --> 00:25:22,000
It's faster already.

355
00:25:25,833 --> 00:25:27,133
It's fast.

356
00:26:04,067 --> 00:26:07,367
I don't understand why
this is happening to us!

357
00:26:07,433 --> 00:26:09,567
We're good people.

358
00:26:09,667 --> 00:26:11,900
Actions speak louder than words.

359
00:26:11,967 --> 00:26:13,467
What are you trying to say?

360
00:26:13,533 --> 00:26:14,967
What was Zandro doing here?

361
00:26:15,033 --> 00:26:16,767
I'm sorry, Dindi.

362
00:26:16,833 --> 00:26:18,833
Your contract won't be renewed.

363
00:26:18,900 --> 00:26:19,500
What?
My feeling's right.

364
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:22,300
Rina has something to do
with this.

365
00:26:22,367 --> 00:26:25,400
She's punishing everyone
around me.

366
00:26:25,467 --> 00:26:27,100
She's so evil!

367
00:26:27,167 --> 00:26:27,900
That's them!

368
00:26:30,500 --> 00:26:32,000
Amanda!

369
00:26:32,067 --> 00:26:34,533
With all the things that
happened to us on this island,

370
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:36,467
I only have one feeling...
